EDITING THE ATTENDANCE REGISTER

If the Learner did not sign the Online Register or wishes to correct his/her Attendance register, then the Learner must approach his/her respective supervisor to make the necessary changes. Only the Supervisor can EDIT the Learner Attendance Register. Learners cannot EDIT the past Attendance. Please request your supervisor to go to PROCESS 1 on the Supervisor Dash Board of the GRANT PORTAL to EDIT the Attendance Register. The Student must include a brief explanation in the Learner COMMENTS box, the reason why the attendance Register needs to be corrected. A Training Plan/Project Management Plan is a roadmap of the projected Training, Learning, or Research milestones that the Learner is required to complete or is required to achieve.
A Training Plan/Project Management Plan is an important planning tool to guide both the Supervisor and the Learner. Supervisors are required to plan the broad areas that Learners need to cover and then decide on the duration and schedule of each.

A Training Plan/Project Management Plan is not a detailed document. It contains basic information such as, what are the planned tasks or activities, the approximate duration of the tasks/activities, and the planned dates. The Program is a dynamic document and may be modified as and when the need arises.
